---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Lou Campos - About">
  <main
    class="flex-grow w-full max-w-[1600px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-12 flex flex-col pt-12 md:pt-24"
  >
    <!-- Hero Header -->
    <section class="mb-24 md:mb-32 max-w-7xl animate-fade-in-up">
      <h2
        class="font-sans font-bold text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl leading-[1.2] text-dark-grey dark:text-white tracking-tight"
      >
        <span class="text-accent-pink">Lou Campos</span> (Córdoba, 1990), explora
        los espacios a través de los conceptos, categorías perceptuales y <span
          class="text-accent-pink">jerarquías visuales</span
        >.
        <br class="block mb-4 md:mb-6" />
        Su práctica genera paisajes y estancias que nos hacen reflexionar acerca de
        la ficcionalidad o realidad de los diferentes elementos, tratando a su vez
        las temáticas de la
        <span class="text-accent-pink">sintiencia animal</span> o el cambio climático.
      </h2>
    </section>

    <!-- Two-Column Grid -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-16 lg:gap-24 pb-32">
      <!-- Left Column: Milestones -->
      <aside
        class="lg:col-span-4 animate-fade-in-up"
        style="animation-delay: 100ms;"
      >
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-12">
          <div class="w-[2px] h-4 bg-accent-pink"></div>
          <h3
            class="font-sans text-[10px] md:text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.2em] text-dark-grey dark:text-white uppercase"
          >
            Milestones
          </h3>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-12 ml-1">
          <!-- Item 1 -->
          <div
            class="relative pl-8 border-l border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800"
          >
            <div
              class="absolute -left-[5px] top-1.5 w-[9px] h-[9px] bg-accent-pink rounded-full opacity-40"
            >
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <span
                class="text-[10px] font-sans font-bold text-accent-pink tracking-wider"
                >2021</span
              >
              <h4
                class="text-lg font-bold text-dark-grey dark:text-white font-sans"
              >
                Luminosity Prize
              </h4>
              <p
                class="text-xs font-serif italic text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500"
              >
                Winner, Contemporary Sculpture Category
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Item 2 -->
          <div
            class="relative pl-8 border-l border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800"
          >
            <div
              class="absolute -left-[5px] top-1.5 w-[9px] h-[9px] bg-accent-pink rounded-full opacity-40"
            >
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <span
                class="text-[10px] font-sans font-bold text-accent-pink tracking-wider"
                >2018</span
              >
              <h4
                class="text-lg font-bold text-dark-grey dark:text-white font-sans"
              >
                Emerging Artist Grant
              </h4>
              <p
                class="text-xs font-serif italic text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500"
              >
                Tokyo Arts Council
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Item 3 -->
          <div
            class="relative pl-8 border-l border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800"
          >
            <div
              class="absolute -left-[5px] top-1.5 w-[9px] h-[9px] bg-accent-pink rounded-full opacity-40"
            >
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <span
                class="text-[10px] font-sans font-bold text-accent-pink tracking-wider"
                >2015</span
              >
              <h4
                class="text-lg font-bold text-dark-grey dark:text-white font-sans"
              >
                MFA, Fine Arts
              </h4>
              <p
                class="text-xs font-serif italic text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500"
              >
                Parsons School of Design, New York
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Item 4 -->
          <div
            class="relative pl-8 border-l border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800"
          >
            <div
              class="absolute -left-[5px] top-1.5 w-[9px] h-[9px] bg-accent-pink rounded-full opacity-40"
            >
            </div>
            <div class="space-y-1">
              <span
                class="text-[10px] font-sans font-bold text-accent-pink tracking-wider"
                >2010</span
              >
              <h4
                class="text-lg font-bold text-dark-grey dark:text-white font-sans"
              >
                BFA, Sculpture
              </h4>
              <p
                class="text-xs font-serif italic text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500"
              >
                Musashino Art University, Tokyo
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- Right Column: Biography -->
      <section
        class="lg:col-span-8 lg:mt-0 animate-fade-in-up"
        style="animation-delay: 200ms;"
      >
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-12">
          <h3
            class="font-sans text-[10px] md:text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.2em] text-dark-grey dark:text-white uppercase text-right w-full lg:text-left"
          >
            Biography
          </h3>
          <div class="lg:hidden w-[2px] h-4 bg-accent-pink"></div>
        </div>

        <div
          class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-invert font-serif text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 max-w-none space-y-8 leading-relaxed"
        >
          <p>
            Lou Campos is a multidisciplinary artist whose work interrogates the
            relationship between digital architecture and physical presence.
            Born in Tokyo and educated in New York, Campos draws upon a diverse
            cultural lexicon to create minimalist sculptures and installations
            that challenge the viewer's perception of space and volume.
          </p>
          <p>
            His creative process often begins with algorithmic generation, using
            code to identify "errors" or "glitches" in perfect geometric
            systems. These digital anomalies are then meticulously rendered into
            physical reality using traditional materials such as marble, steel,
            and untreated wood. This juxtaposition creates a dialogue between
            the cold precision of technology and the warm, tactile nature of
            craft.
          </p>
          <blockquote
            class="border-l-2 border-accent-pink pl-10 my-16 italic text-2xl text-dark-grey dark:text-white leading-snug"
          >
            "I am interested in the moment a perfect system fails. That fracture
            is where humanity lives."
          </blockquote>
          <p>
            Campos's work has been exhibited internationally, with major
            installations in Tokyo, London, and Berlin. His series <em
              >Structure 01</em
            > was widely acclaimed for its innovative use of light as a structural
            material, creating "walls" that vanish when approached. He continues to
            live and work in Tokyo, where the dense urban landscape serves as a constant
            source of inspiration for his studies on confinement and liberation.
          </p>
          <p>
            Currently, he is developing a new body of work that incorporates
            bio-feedback data to alter the physical shape of kinetic sculptures
            in real-time, further blurring the line between the observer and the
            observed.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
